# Secure Python / FastAPI Development

## Authentication & authorization

- Every admin/clinical route MUST use `get_current_user` and role checks via `require_roles` or domain RBAC helpers
- Public write endpoints (e.g. `/public/enquiries`) MUST be rate-limited and input-validated; never expose internal fields
- WebSocket connections MUST validate JWT before accept

## SQL & data

- Use SQLAlchemy ORM or parameterized `text()` with bound params — never f-string SQL with user input
- Validate UUIDs and enums at schema layer before DB access

## Secrets

- No hardcoded credentials, API keys, or JWT secrets in source
- Use `get_settings()` from config; document in `.env.example` only

## Input validation

- All request bodies via Pydantic schemas with field constraints
- Normalize phone numbers via `normalize_phone()` before storage

## Error handling

- Use `AppError` with safe messages; do not leak stack traces or SQL in responses

## File & path operations

- Presigned uploads only via `/storage/presign`; validate content-type and size
- Reject path traversal in any user-supplied file paths

## External HTTP

- SSRF: whitelist outbound URLs for integrations; no arbitrary fetch from user input
